Each subsequent level represents a huge increase in the geometry of space from the previous level.
Our universe can have additional dimensions (we see them at the fourth level of enlargement) if they're confined to a sufficiently small space; that explains why we haven't directly observed them yet.
The quadrangle represents the commonly known "big" dimensions, while the circles represent a new, tiny, dirty dimension.
