If the additional circular curved dimension is extremely small, it is much harder to recognize it - as is the circular circumference of a pipe - than to observe the apparent, large, and expansive dimensions.
If the size of the extra dimension is small enough, it will actually reveal it beyond the power of our most advanced magnification tools.
Most importantly, however, the extra dimension is not just a round pile inside normal dimensions, as the two-dimensional illustration mistakenly suggests.
A circular dimension is a new dimension that exists at each point of the three common extended dimensions.
